---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words With Double G — STAGGERING, SUGGEST, JOGGING & More"
  description="Best double-G words for Scrabble. JOGGING (17pts), SUGGEST (10pts), STAGGERING. GG pattern strategy for consistent mid-game plays. Free word finder."
  keywords="scrabble double g words, jogging scrabble, suggest scrabble, staggering scrabble, gg words scrabble, double g strategy, double letter words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words With Double G — STAGGERING, SUGGEST, JOGGING & More",
    "description": "Best double-G Scrabble words. GG pattern strategy for mid-game plays.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-g" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best double-G words in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "JOGGING (17pts with J=8), SUGGEST (10pts), and STAGGERING. GG words pair naturally with -ING suffix for bingos." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many G tiles are in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "3 G tiles (2pts each). Drawing two gives 4 points from G alone, plus natural -ING suffix patterns." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What -GG- patterns work?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Common: -OGGING (jogging, logging), -AGGING (bagging, lagging), -IGGING (digging, rigging), -UGGEST (suggest)." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Double G — STAGGERING, SUGGEST, JOGGING & More</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>4 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Three G tiles in the bag (2pts each) means GG pairs appear regularly. The best part? GG words pair naturally with the -ING suffix, creating bingo-length plays from familiar everyday words.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JOGGING</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SUGGEST</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Per GG pair</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">G tiles in bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Double-G Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top GG Word</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JOGGING — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">J=8, O=1, G=2, G=2, I=1, N=1, G=2 · 7 letters · Bingo eligible</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">J=8 powers this familiar word. With bingo bonus, JOGGING scores 67 total — using three G tiles for maximum rack clearance.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💡 SUGGEST</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · 7 letters · GG + S pair · Bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🥚 EGGNOG</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · 6 letters · Double GG pattern</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎒 LUGGAGE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · 7 letters · GG mid-word</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏃 JOGGING</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 pts · 7 letters · J=8 + triple G</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">GG Pattern Strategy</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">GG + ING = bingo factory:</span> LOGGING, FOGGING, HUGGING, DIGGING — add -ING to any -GG root for 7-letter bingos. One of the most reliable bingo paths.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">EGG as a hook starter:</span> EGG extends to EGGNOG, EGGING. Play it early near open board space for later extensions.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pair GG with J:</span> JOGGING (17pts), JIGGING (17pts) — J=8 plus GG creates explosive plays without needing full bingo length.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LOGGING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DIGGING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HUGGING</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BIGGEST</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Suffix Synergy</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">GG + ING uses <span class="text-white font-medium">3 of the 3 available G tiles</span>. Holding all three? A -GGING word clears your entire G inventory in one bingo play.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-t/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Double T</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ing/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -ING</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find double-G words from your rack — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
